 The carnage caused by some fossil fuels are the DIRECT result of the &quot;grandfathered&quot; methods they are allowed to use. (NOT THAT I DESIRE ANY NEW FOSSIL FUEL USE)<br>
<br>
Fusion, if possible, has many positives, but (unless some REAL microscale system can be created), will carry all the negatives of big biz/big gov/centralized/expensive, ~and~ be a source of a tidal wave of U233 and Pu239. Think of the thread on Yugoslaviia's 48 kilograms of U235 and then imagine a world where the production of KILOTONS of U235 and Pu239 is a YEARLY event - with 5 kilograms enough to shatter a city.<br>
<br>
Long before the first (potentially impossible) fusion plant comes on line, PVs integrated into structures will displace any market.<br>
<br>
Remember what Lovins pointed out in the RMI article?<br>
A pound of silicon provides more energy as a solar cell than a pound of Uranium in an light water reactor.<br>
<br>
