c future, it is an unavoidable fact of the very nature of the Universe that U235 or Pu239 can be fissioned slowly in a reactor, but also reacted quickly in a bomb. There is simply NOTHING that we can do to change that FACT. The Universe does not operate on Disney's First Law: &quot;Wishing will make it so&quot;<br>
<br>
 What things like fusion reactors and other large neutron sources do (such as fission reactors or large accelerators), is breed more fissionables from  such cheap common substances such as U238 or Thorium232. Even if you sent all the fissionables on Earth directly into the Sun, a fusion reactor would replace them in a jif.<br>
<br>
yale<br>
